pktcEUERSTMIB.description: This MIB module contains configuration MIB objects for supporting RST Features specified in the PacketCable RST specification.

PktcRSTTCTONEANNC.name: PktcRSTTCTONEANNC
PktcRSTTCTONEANNC.description: This TEXTUAL CONVENTION is being defined as a way of indicating the announcement. If it is an URI, it is represented as a hex string representing the URI.

PktcRSTTCFeatID.name: PktcRSTTCFeatID
PktcRSTTCFeatID.description: This TEXTUAL CONVENTION is being defined as a way to enumerate the RST features.

PktcEUETCRSTAppPrfIndexType.name: PktcEUETCRSTAppPrfIndexType
PktcEUETCRSTAppPrfIndexType.description: This TEXTUAL CONVENTION is being defined to indicate any indices related to RST Application Profiles. Such an instance can be referenced across tables to indicate an association.

PktcEUETCRSTAppFeatIndexType.name: PktcEUETCRSTAppFeatIndexType
PktcEUETCRSTAppFeatIndexType.description: This TEXTUAL CONVENTION is being defined to indicate any indices related to RST Application Features. Such an instance can be referenced across tables to indicate an association.

pktcEUERSTProfileVersion.name: pktcEUERSTProfileVersion
pktcEUERSTProfileVersion.description: This MIB Object represents the RST Profile Version for this MIB module. The eUE MUST set this MIB Object to a value of '1.0'.

pktcEUERSTAppProfileToFeatTable.name: pktcEUERSTAppProfileToFeatTable
pktcEUERSTAppProfileToFeatTable.description: This table specifies RST profiles that can be associated with Users supporting the RST application.

pktcEUERSTAppProfileToFeatEntry.name: pktcEUERSTAppProfileToFeatEntry
pktcEUERSTAppProfileToFeatEntry.description: Each entry in this table specifies an RST profile associated with a set of RST features.

pktcEUERSTAppProfileIndex.name: pktcEUERSTAppProfileIndex
pktcEUERSTAppProfileIndex.description: This MIB Object identifies an instance of an RST application profile.

pktcEUERSTAppFeatIndex.name: pktcEUERSTAppFeatIndex
pktcEUERSTAppFeatIndex.description: This MIB Object identifies a specific RST feature instance.

pktcEUERSTAppFeatID.name: pktcEUERSTAppFeatID
pktcEUERSTAppFeatID.description: The MIB Object identifies a specific RST feature, as specified by PacketCable RST.

pktcEUERSTAppFeatIndexRef.name: pktcEUERSTAppFeatIndexRef
pktcEUERSTAppFeatIndexRef.description: The MIB Object identifies an index into the RST feature table identified by the MIB Object pktcEUERSTAppFeatID. A value of '0' is reserved and is used to either identify a global feature configuration, or when no configuration data is specified for the feature. Setting the value to '0' in any other cases will result in feature configuration error.

pktcEUERSTAppNwActStat.name: pktcEUERSTAppNwActStat
pktcEUERSTAppNwActStat.description: The status of this feature as determined by the Network. The default value is true(1).

pktcEUERSTAppNwActStatInfo.name: pktcEUERSTAppNwActStatInfo
pktcEUERSTAppNwActStatInfo.description: This MIB Object MAY provide more information about the status reported by the MIB Object pktcEUERSTAppNwActStat.

pktcEUERSTAppEUEActStat.name: pktcEUERSTAppEUEActStat
pktcEUERSTAppEUEActStat.description: The status of this feature as determined by the eUE.

pktcEUERSTAppEUEActStatInfo.name: pktcEUERSTAppEUEActStatInfo
pktcEUERSTAppEUEActStatInfo.description: This MIB Object MAY provide more information about the status reported by the MIB Object pktcEUERSTAppUEActStat.

pktcEUERSTAppRowActStatus.name: pktcEUERSTAppRowActStatus
pktcEUERSTAppRowActStatus.description: This MIB Object defines the row status associated with this particular application profile in the MIB table. An entry in this table is not qualified for activation until the object instances of all corresponding columns have been initialized, either by default values or via explicit SET operations. Until all object instances in this row are initialized, the status value for this realm must be 'notReady(3)'. In particular, two columnar objects must be SET: the 'pktcEUERSTAppFeatID' and 'pktcEUERSTAppFeatIndexRef'. Once these two objects have been set the row status may be SET to 'active(1)'. The eUE MUST not allow these two objects to be changed while the row is 'active'. The value of this object has no effect on whether other columnar objects in this row can be modified.
